title: How did patients feel about how quickly they received care from out-of-hours GP service?
analysis_commentary: Overall the majority (greater than 60%) of patients surveyed thought the time it took to receive care from the out-of-hours GP service was about right, however, there has been a slight decrease from 63% in 2011/12 to 61% between July 2014 and March 2015.
